I don't mind paying more for quality food but out of the food I tried the "bucket of fries" was the best and that's sad for a restaurant that claims to be inspired by french cuisine. I guess if you're looking to "be seen" it's a good spot but if you're looking for good food and not to be hungry in an hour go literally anywhere else.

Love this dunkin donuts and baskin robbins ice cream 31 spot!  This one has the most clean atmosphere, tasty goodies and good-service staffs unlike some small franchises where you are greeted with unhappy staffs with attitude. This one is not like that!  Coffee is good and fresh and ice cream taste great all the time. They were selling baskin robbins voucher $5 for five one scoop ice cream cone and I am taking advantage of that as I love their cheery jubillee and green pistachio! Not to mention it is a big saving 50-60% off deal? :)  I am glad I live near by and I can stop by here for delicious and fresh goodies when I am hungry.
